## Auth Code Exchange Flow

1. User visits consumer app -> `DedgeAuthRedirectMiddleware` redirects to `/DedgeAuth/login.html?returnUrl=...`
2. User logs in at DedgeAuth -> JWT + short-lived auth code
3. DedgeAuth redirects back to consumer app with `?code=<authCode>`
4. `DedgeAuthTokenExtractionMiddleware` exchanges code server-to-server via `POST /api/auth/exchange`
5. JWT stored in `DedgeAuth_access_token` cookie, browser redirected to clean URL
6. `DedgeAuthSessionValidationMiddleware` validates session via `GET /api/auth/validate` (cached 30s)
7. On cache miss, fires-and-forgets `POST /api/visits/record` to record the visit

## Middleware Pipeline (consumer apps)

```
DedgeAuthTokenExtractionMiddleware   -> extracts ?code= or ?token= or cookie -> sets Authorization header
UseAuthentication                 -> JWT validation
UseAuthorization                  -> policy evaluation
DedgeAuthSessionValidationMiddleware -> validates with DedgeAuth server, records visits
DedgeAuthRedirectMiddleware          -> redirects unauthenticated to login
```

All registered by `app.UseDedgeAuth()`. Do NOT call `UseAuthentication()`/`UseAuthorization()` separately.

## UI Asset Proxy

Consumer HTML uses **relative paths** (no leading `/`) to load DedgeAuth assets through `MapDedgeAuthProxy()`:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="api/DedgeAuth/ui/common.css">
<style id="DedgeAuth-tenant-css"></style>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="api/DedgeAuth/ui/user.css">
<div id="DedgeAuthUserMenu"></div>
<script src="api/DedgeAuth/ui/user.js"></script>
```

`DedgeAuth-user.js` handles: user menu, app switcher, tenant CSS/logo/favicon injection, visit history link. Changes to DedgeAuth wwwroot propagate to all apps without rebuild.

