## IIS Deploy Commands

```powershell
# Redeploy all (teardown + iisreset + rebuild from templates)
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-RedeployAll.ps1"

# Deploy single app
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-DeployApp.ps1" -SiteName <AppName>

# Uninstall single app
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-UninstallApp.ps1" -SiteName <AppName>

# Diagnose broken app
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\Test-IISSite.ps1" -SiteName <AppName>
```

## Impact Rules

- **DedgeAuth.Client change** -> `Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1` (all apps need updated DLL)
- **DedgeAuth wwwroot change** -> rebuild DedgeAuth only (consumers fetch via proxy)
- **Tenant branding** -> update `tenants` table only, no rebuild
- **Deploy template change** -> run `IIS-DeployApp\_deploy.ps1` to sync to servers
- **Single consumer app change** -> rebuild that app only, then `IIS-DeployApp.ps1 -SiteName <AppName>`
